# Components & Styling

## Components

- Functional components only; export named (not default) except Expo Router route files.
- PascalCase file + component name for UI (`Button.tsx`). Co-locate styles in the same file.
- Type props inline or with a local `type Props = {...}`. Prefer composition; build on shared primitives (`Screen`, `Card`, `Button`, `TextField`, `Badge`).
- Wrap screen content in `<Screen>` so safe-area insets + background are handled consistently.

## Styling

- Use `StyleSheet.create` at the bottom of the file. No inline style objects for anything non-trivial.
- NEVER hardcode colors, spacing, or radii. Always pull from the design system:

```tsx
import { Colors } from '../utils/colors';
import { Radius, Spacing, Typography } from '../utils/theme';

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  card: { backgroundColor: Colors.surface, borderRadius: Radius.card, padding: Spacing.cardPadding },
});
```

- New colors/spacing/type scales must be added to `shared/utils/colors.ts` or `theme.ts` first, then referenced.
- Icons: `@expo/vector-icons` (`Ionicons`), tint with `Colors`.
- Account for safe areas via `useSafeAreaInsets()` / `<Screen>`; never assume fixed top/bottom padding.
